	                  Z-POP v1.1

	Copyright (C) 1993-1998 NetManage Software.

This distribution contains the Z-POP server.

Z-POP is an enhanced version of the POP3 protocol, and zpop
is a Unix implementation of a Z-POP server.

For quick installation instructions, see the file INSTALL.TXT.
For detailed installation and configuration information, see the
file CONFIG.TXT.

********* SPECIAL NOTE FOR MMDF SYSTEMS **********

Z-POP does not currently handle MMDF-style folders.  This is a known
problem, PR #6328 in our bug-tracking system.  Until that is fixed,
you can only use Z-POP if you are using a mail transport agent such 
as sendmail that uses V7-style folders.
